{
  "text": "Do these findings have translational implications for rescue of GSIS in T2D? Importantly, the ability of glucose to drive insulin granule exocytosis in patch-clamped normal human \u03b2-cells is lost in \u03b2-cells from human donors with T2D. However, infusion of isocitrate or NAPDH rescues the exocytotic response in these cells. [CITATION_1] These findings suggest that islets from humans with T2D may be defective at a step (or steps) of anaplerotic metabolism of glucose upstream of the IDH1 reaction. Further studies will be required to define the specific molecular lesions in anaplerotic metabolism of glucose in islets from T2D subjects.",
  "citation_candidates": [
